[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'sirinath', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 03:25:38+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "Is it possible to maybe liaison with GitHub/GitLab to remove API limits? This will be more convenient than hosting one's own instance.

Also, get sponsorship from them or another provider supporting static sites towards the Staticman site hosting if hosting bandwidth and power is a limiting factor.", 'title': 'Appeal to Remove API Limits and Get Support Towards Hosted Instance of Staticman', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'alexwaibel', 'comment_id': 654291352.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 15:00:16+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'The issue is not an API limit from GitHub. The reason the public instance was discontinued was that it was hosted on the free tier of Heroku which has low usage limit. With multiple people trying to use the same public instance, we quickly exhausted the limits of that Heroku tier. This is a community project with no funding so unless we find someone to pay for a public instance, the best alternative is to streamline the Staticman setup process and encourage users to host their own free instance.

Sponsorship is something we are open to, however I currently do not have the time to go out and search for such a sponsor.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'sirinath', 'comment_id': 654302129.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 15:19:24+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'You can just ask Heroku to remove the limits. If they do then great win for everyone.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'alexwaibel', 'comment_id': 654324473.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 15:59:53+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "Heroku is a business and has no incentive to offer us unlimited free hosting for nothing in return. We don't really have any leverage in this situation.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'sirinath', 'comment_id': 654325651.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 16:01:58+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'You can put a sponsored by Heroku on the website and the readme.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'sirinath', 'comment_id': 654331186.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 16:12:33+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Companies like GitHub, GitLab, Zeit, Netlify may have the incentive to host it as this will increase adaptation of their services and will be added benefit to their clients.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'alexwaibel', 'comment_id': 654337258.0, 'datetime': '2020-07-06 16:23:54+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "As mentioned before, I personally don't currently have the time to seek out such potential sponsorships so this is not something I plan to pursue. This project is currently in a kind of a maintenance mode where I attempt to get to critical bug fixes in a timely manner but don't have the bandwidth to add features and expand the project further right now. If we get some more maintainers and development of this project picks up steam, then I think we would be in a better position to seek sponsorship. If anyone is interested in such a role, we will happily accept contributions.

Having a sponsor places certain expectations on the project (especially regarding feature development) and this is just not something we're in a position to commit to at this time.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'VincentTam', 'comment_id': 792634755.0, 'datetime': '2021-03-08 09:56:53+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "With the one-click deploy button and the updated tutorials, hosting on a free-tier Heroku should be incredibly convenient with no installation at all.

Take Git*'s API limit as the fuse box of your floor.  In case of a short circuit (say sœÅŒ±m), the circuit has to be cut.  As a commenting service hosted on a particular instance can be used by everyone, this safety guard has to be put in place.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}]

[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2018-03-16T13:11:24Z', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '`delete` was deprecated in 2.079.  Before the `delete` keyword can be removed it will be necessary to also deprecate and remove class allocators and deallocators.  They have been planned for deprecation for years; this PR finally puts the deprecation process in motion.

See https://dlang.org/deprecate.html#Class%20allocators%20and%20deallocators

DMD PR:  https://github.com/dlang/dmd/pull/8042', 'title': 'Deprecate class allocators and deallocators', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'adamdruppe', 'comment_id': 373713612.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 13:30:54+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'So we recently found `@disable new` is actually kinda cool....', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 373714050.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 13:32:48+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Please elaborate.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'adamdruppe', 'comment_id': 373715364.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 13:37:47+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': '```
struct S
{
  @disable new (size_t s) { return null; }
}

void main()
{
	S* s = new S; //  Error: allocator `e.S.new` is not callable because it is annotated with @disable
}
```', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'adamdruppe', 'comment_id': 373715994.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 13:40:12+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'So the application there is you can force users to go through your custom factory functions, or in the case of structs, put them on the stack (or bypass with memcpy lol).', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JackStouffer', 'comment_id': 373718495.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 13:49:30+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'See https://github.com/dlang/phobos/pull/6003 for an example.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 373834833.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 20:25:10+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "I've added support for the syntax `@disable new();` to the DMD PR.  You won't even need to add the useless `size_t` argument.  That should prevent any breaking changes.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'adamdruppe', 'comment_id': 373835584.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-16 20:27:58+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'That sounds good to me!', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 373888991.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-17 02:48:22+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Great!  If you don't mind, and truly approve of this PR, please take the explicit step of marking it "Approved".', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'adamdruppe', 'comment_id': 373889129.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-17 02:51:12+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "oh lol i keep forgetting i actually have some power in this repo. I don't have such power over on the dmd side though.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 373889456.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-17 02:57:27+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'I still think it's helpful to mark PRs "approved" even in repos where you may not have merge rights.  It helps to know that it was reviewed and scrutinized by anyone with D language skills, especially a veteran like yourself.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'wilzbach', 'comment_id': 373988978.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-18 10:58:54+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': "Shouldn't this PR remove or mark as deprecated the respective sections in the spec too?
e.g.
https://dlang.org/spec/class.html#allocators", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 373992927.0, 'datetime': '2018-03-18 12:01:48+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'I remember a brief discussion we had with one of the other deprecations in 2.079 to leave the spec in tact until removal (See https://github.com/dlang/dlang.org/pull/1941#issuecomment-364106970) so users could still refer to it when updating their code.  Therefore, since the spec has already marked allocators and deallocators as deprecated, I think the spec should be left it as is until removal.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'JinShil', 'comment_id': 377780339.0, 'datetime': '2018-04-01 11:29:04+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Ping!  DMD PR was merged.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}]
